entry.title: Add minimum value for raster scale.
entry.content:
With raster slop, there is degenerate exponential updating behaviour

as raster scale tends towards 0. The `kMinimumRasterScale` value

denotes a minimum value for raster scale. This is set such that the

largest windows we expect (e.g. on 4k displays) can still have their

raster scales reduced down so the width and height of their buffers

is on the order of a few hundred pixels at most.

entry.title: Stop storing Print Preview request data in PrintPreviewUI
entry.content:
Since the Print Preview UI can be reloaded in some rare cases, the

PrintPreviewUI instance that runs the UI can get destroyed and

recreated. If this happens, PrintPreviewUI will lose track of some

values and hand out potentially incorrect values.



Prevent this situation from happening by storing the Print Preview

request data in PrintPreviewDialogController instead. Divert all data

getters/setters to use the new data source. PrintPreviewDialogController

already keeps track of all print preview requests, and it is immune to

Print Preview UI reloads.



To keep the existing PrintPreviewHandlerTest working, add some test-only

calls to (dis)associate WebContentses, as the test manually creates its

own.



To keep tests that navigate directly to chrome://print working, allow

PrintPreviewHandler to use dummy request data when

PrintPreviewDialogController does not know about the Print Preview.



Do some cleanups along the way, to tidy things up. In particular,

avoid including Print Preview headers when Print Preview is not

available.

entry.title: Only update raster scale on windows on large changes
entry.content:
This CL adds a raster scale slop parameter to RasterScaleController.

Raster scale won't be updated for a window unless the currently

requested raster scale is more than `raster_scale_slop_proportion_`

different by proportion to the currently set value. As a special case,

requesting the raster scale to 1.0 will always update the raster scale

window property. This is to prevent windows from getting stuck in

non-1.0f raster scales when all `ScopedSetRasterScale`s are released.

AVCaptureDevice:

entry.title: macOS: simplify immersive fullscreen implementation.
entry.content:
The original implementation of immersive fullscreen created a dummy

BridgedContentView that reused the original bridge. At the time it was

necessary for tab dragging and selection of omnibox text while the

dropdown was showing. This is no longer the case. This CL simplifies the

logic to use an opaque NSView.



Being opaque is necessary for the toolbar/tabstrip to render anything at

all. It's not immediately clear why this is necessary since the NSView

typically has a size of (0, 0). Perhaps some intrinsic AppKit

limitations? Either way, using an opaque NSView is much simpler than

creating a new BridgedContentView with a reused bridge.

entry.title: views: Fix bug in Widget::Show.
entry.content:
The purpose of Widget is to propagate state between views (Chrome's

native UI toolkit) and the native drawing surface (aka NativeWidget).



The previous implementation of Widget::Show() was incorrectly

propagating state from NativeWidget back to NativeWidget.

```

native_widget_->Show(

IsFullscreen() ? ui::SHOW_STATE_FULLSCREEN : saved_show_state_,

```

Widget::IsFullscreen() fetches state from NativeWidget. The previous

logic was equivalent to:

(1) If the native surface is fullscreen, show it and make it fullscreen

again.

(2) Otherwise, show the native surface with saved_show_state_.



This CL skips (1) entirely. The core takeaway is that if views is

calling Show(), then the NativeWidget should not be currently showing,

which also means it cannot currently be fullscreen.

entry.title: Fix SW static routing API running status condition.
entry.content:
In the past implementation, we used the cached value for the running

status when it is asked inside the ServiceWorkerSubresourceLoader.

It is a bit stale value and the caller may get too old value to use.

This CL makes the value updated on ServiceWorkerVersion's running status

change to avoid such mismatch as much as possible. For that purpose,

when the ServiceWorker static routing rules have rules with

running status condition, a mojo IPC receiver is created and passed

to the controller ServiceWorker connector to make the connector to be

the receiver of the running status.



We also fixed the test. The test expects the ServiceWorker has been

stopped. However, after `ReloadBlockUntilNavigationsComplete` is

called, the ServiceWorker awakes, and we need to explicitly stop it

to make the test work.

entry.title: arc/gio: Release all touch events when mouse interrupts
entry.content:
There is an issue on Android side that both mouse events and touch

events are instances of MotionEvent. When the touch MotionEvent is

active and mouse MotionEvent interrupts, the previous touch MotionEvent

is generated as a cancel event, which puts some games in a weird state.

For example, the character may keep running without stop.



This CL:

- Adds an extra touch release event to finish the previous touch

MotionEvent onAndroid side before sending mouse events to solve this

issue.

- Replaces DispatchTouchCancelEvent by DispatchTouchReleaseEvent to

avoid future issues like this.

entry.content:
The current encryption implementation in the encryptor uses the system

salt as both a key and a nonce, which is not good. This adds a new

version of the encrypt and decrypt functions which uses a random nonce

instead just puts in place the support needed to enable updating the

calling code. It does not actually attempt to change said code.

entry.title: Fix perf regression in AnchorElementMetricsSender when checking for a secure context
entry.content:
A recent change introduced the use of IsUrlPotentiallyTrustworthy to

determine whether a document with an HTTP URL could create a

AnchorElementMetricsSender, such as the case of localhost. This involved

making a copy of the URL to pass to the function, which can be expensive,

especially given that in some cases, this code is on a hot path (e.g. pages

with tens of thousands of anchors). We now use a method which gets the

same information in constant time.

entry.title: IndexedDB: remove some more bucket thread to main thread deps
entry.content:
Directly notify the quota manager of bucket access when closing or

opening connections. The QuotaManagerProxy is thread safe.



Previously, when opening a new connection, the main context would also

query the disk to get an updated usage calculation. However, this

should not be necessary as it's redundant with FactoryOpened().



Likewise, when closing a connection, if it was the last connection, the

context would recalculate usage. This would have been redundant with

TransactionComplete().



Some already-stale includes are also cleaned up.

entry.title: [Test Automation] ExecuteJs[At], CheckJs[At] fail on error
entry.content:
Previously, ExecuteJs, ExecuteJsAt, CheckJs, and CheckJsAt could swallow

relevant error information if an exception was thrown, or (in the case

of the ...At() versions) if the element was not present.



This rewrites the JS injection logic for these methods so that all

errors are caught and explicitly surfaced as test failures, with their

JS error messages. This includes any of:

- DeepQuery path not found

- Exception thrown by injected function

- Injected function returns a promise which then calls 'reject'



In order to handle the case where executed JS may destroy or navigate the current web page, an optional "fire and forget" mode is added to ExecuteJs[At] which preserves the old behavior (though you will not get error checking in that case).



Numerous tests ensuring functionality are also added.
